Articles.Content:
Downloaded via store. Launched via Launcher and KSP.app (including a test in Low Res mode and 32-bit mode). Upon launch, screen is 640x480 and all text/graphics are highly aliased. Went to settings to attempt to change size, and it is locked at Custom. Attempted full-screen mode and Accept/Apply functions do not respond. Window won't scale to allow for further attempt to change size as text is cut-off.

Attempted to play Sandbox mode normal (to see if game would load beyond start screen) and after over five minutes of black screen and spinning wheel, I closed the app (via Force Quit -- KSP [not responding]). 

App is unplayable from a variety of perspectives. Looks like a large volume of errors in the log. Again, this is a vanilla, fresh install of the latest build downloaded at 12PM MST 4/20.

Thanks!

Update: Modified the settings.cfg file to change the default values (which were at 640x480). Was able to startup app with an appropriate resolution however app still crashes upon starting Sandbox requiring a Force Quit.

Edited April 20, 2016 by moprosk
Added description of further attempts and log.

I had a similar problem. Game started in lowest resolution - which meant that half the graphics sliders were missing due to being off-screen, including the slider to change resolution. Well played, Squad - well played. Fortunately, changing the resolution from the Launcher fixed that.

Have you tried switching off the anti-aliasing? That worked for me. Makes the game look that bit uglier but better than having no game at all.

I ended up re-downloading the game and the file size was about 100MB larger - it seems they initially released a build that wasn't complete. Sadly, this newest build has plenty of issues, too. I was able to get it going but now the KSP keeps freezing about five minutes in, regardless of whether it's a scene change, simply time passing, in a tutorial or playing career mode.  I let it run frozen for about five minutes before force closing it. Game is still unplayable for me!
